1)What is Python? What are the ways to install python in your PC?
Ans:
Python is an interpreted, high-level, general-purpose programming language. Created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991 and became popular in 2006.

-->Ways to install python in PC:
   Python Can be installed from :-

   * From Python official website i.e. www.python.org
   * From Anaconda Navigator official website i.e www.anaconda.com
   * From PyCharm IDE i.e. www.jetbrains.com/pycharm
   * Using Google colab you can implement python codes without downloading, as it is cloud based.


2)What are code enviroment? Types?
Ans:
A code environment is a standalone and self-contained environment to run Python code. In each location where you can run Python or R code, you can select which code environment to use.
Code environements are the platforms where people can develop or write code, compile the code, see the expected output and
performance of the code with their desired programming langauge installed in system through the packages in the environments.

Types:-
1. Text Editors
Ex: Notepad
2. Integrated Development Environment(IDE)
Ex:- Spyder
3. Notebook Environment
Ex: Jupyter
